name: typeform-create-form
description: Creates a form with its corresponing fields. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/create-form/)

name: typeform-create-image
description: Adds an image in your Typeform account. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/create-image/)

image.description: Base64 code for the image. Note that base64 encoders may add descriptors to the code (such as `data:image/png;base64,`). Do not include these descriptors in your image string---include only the base64 code. We also recommend that you don't paste the exact string value into this property box. Instead you can [pass an expression](https://pipedream.com/docs/workflows/steps/params/#entering-expressions) that references a variable from a previous step such as `{{steps.nodejs.$return_value}}`.

url.description: URL of the image to be added in your Typeform account

name: typeform-delete-form
description: Select a form to be deleted. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/delete-form/).

name: typeform-delete-image
description: Deletes an image from your Typeform account. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/delete-image/)

imageId.description: Unique ID for the image to be deleted

name: typeform-duplicate-form
description: Duplicates an existing form in your Typeform account and adds "(copy)" to the end of the title. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/create-form/)

name: typeform-get-form
description: Select a specific form to get the data. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/retrieve-form/)

name: typeform-list-forms
description: Retrieves a list of forms. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/retrieve-forms/)

pageSize.description: Number of results to retrieve per page. Default is 10. Maximum is 200.

name: typeform-list-images
description: Retrieves a list of JSON descriptions for all images in your Typeform account. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/retrieve-images-collection/)

name: typeform-list-responses
description: Returns form responses and date and time of form landing and submission. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/responses/reference/retrieve-responses/)

includedResponseIds.description: Limit request to the specified `response_id` values. Use a comma-separated list to specify more than one `response_id` value. Please bear in mind that if you set a list of included response ids you won't be able to use the list of excluded response ids

excludedResponseIds.description: Comma-separated list of `response_ids` to be excluded from the response. Please bear in mind that if you set a list of excluded response ids you won't be able to use the list of included response ids

completed.description: Limit responses only to those which were submitted. This parameter changes `since`/`until` filter, so if `completed=true`, it will filter by `submitted_at`, otherwise - `landed_at`.

sort.description: Responses order in `{fieldID},{asc|desc}` format. You can use built-in `submitted_at`/`landed_at` field IDs or any field ID from your typeform, possible directions are `asc`/`desc`. Default value is `submitted_at,desc`.

fields.description: Show only specified fields in answers section. If response does not have answers for specified fields, there will be `null`. Use a comma-separated list to specify more than one field value.

answeredFields.description: Limit request to only responses that include the specified fields in answers section. Use a comma-separated list to specify more than one field value - response will contain at least one of the specified fields.

name: typeform-lookup-responses
description: Search for responses with the `query` property. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/responses/reference/retrieve-responses/)

name: typeform-update-dropdown-multiple-choice-ranking
description: Update a dropdown, multiple choice, or ranking field's choices. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/update-form/)

fieldId.description: Select the question whose choices you'd like to modify.

choice.description: Add the new choice, which will be added to the end of the existing choices for this question.

name: typeform-update-form-title
description: Updates an existing form's title. [See the docs here](https://developer.typeform.com/create/reference/update-form-patch/)
